# Stock media downloaded for social posts (large binaries, not source)
social_agent/assets/media/

# Google Ads exports / personal account data (not source)
google_ads/data/*.csv
google_ads/data/tracking_backup/

# Audit CSV outputs (generated)
audit_current.csv
audit_results.csv

# Internal automation dirs — root keeps these on disk (untracked) for its
# own operation, but they must never be tracked on the shared branch that
# html/'s clone also pulls from, since wrangler pages deploy uploads
# whatever's physically in html/'s working tree with no ignore mechanism
# of its own (.assetsignore's *.py rule is NOT honored by `wrangler pages
# deploy html` — confirmed twice now: this exact list of "core tools" was
# previously assumed safe to keep tracked because they "never had html/
# copies," but a 2026-07-18 live-HTTP-check found all of them serving 200
# on production. Corrected: these are now untracked here too, same as
# everything else in this block. Re-verify this assumption never again —
# always live-check before excluding new scripts from this list.
agents/
social_agent/
google_ads/
infrastructure/
dashboard/
pages/
templates/
affiliate_toolkit/
